                <h2 style="text-align: center">Why Magnetic Rakes?</h2>
                <br />
                <p >
                Magnetic raking is the process of raking a surface in order to attract metallic objects on the surface. The rakes would be ideally attached to rovers that could drag them across the surface of the asteroid.
                The rovers could be driven by humans or be remotely controlled. The magnetic raking mission would start by sending a few rovers with rakes attached to them. Once their rakes are full on material, they would 
                need to be retrieved by another vehicle and taken to a central location. Once their would be enough material collected, a ship would launch back to earth with all of the collected material and rovers.
                </p>
            </div>
